latestPosts.caption:
Every time I take a deep breath and look around at where I am today, I’m reminded that none of this happened by chance.

I’m here because of my mom,  because of the strength, courage, and countless sacrifices she made to give me a life full of opportunity. She left behind the familiar, endured uncertainty, worked harder than anyone should have to, and never gave up just so I could have a better future.

Being in the U.S. isn’t something I take for granted. I know what it cost her, and I carry that with me every single day. Her story is the foundation of mine. I wake up every morning determined to make her sacrifices worth it. 

I’m not just grateful to be here I’m honored. Honored to live the life my mother fought so hard for, and I’ll never forget what it took to get here. This journey is bigger than me, and I owe it all to her.

R.I.P to my tias that immigrated here during the same time🫶✨ only god knows what they went through.

Grateful for the village that raised me🤍

Her strength taught me resilience, and her journey shaped my empathy. I’ll always carry that with me.

It’s why I’ll never forget that there are people out there still struggling, still fighting, and why I’ll always do my best to appreciate what I have and live with compassion.

#gratitude #compassion #love #mexican #immigrants #storytime #aboutme #freedom #living
#latina #present #adversity #la #sd

latestPosts.caption:
I gave this advice to this girl I met at the store

She was telling me how she wanted to start her Instagram and post, and telling me her goals.

I told her to do what she wants, have fun with it because if you overcomplicate things, your inspiration will start to decrease and as long as you don’t let outside criticisms get to you, you will be fine.

#confidenceiskey #adviceforlife

1. Youngest of 6 siblings
